track_notes:
If you want to combine these with Ben Rinnes, you can set off from the same car park.

There is a path the whole way and easy to follow. The initial ascent is steep then more gentle towards Meikle Conval summit. 

Continue over the hill, down the other side and join the path up Little Conval. There is a land rover track that winds up Little Conval if you want a gentler slope. Several cairns on the top of Little Conval.

Return can either be by back over Meikle Conval (possibly shorter) or alongside it, adjacent to the forest. You rejoin the road and walk back to the car park from there.
track_title: Both Convals from Ben Rinnes car park

track_notes:
If you want to combine both Convals with Ben Rinnes, you can set off from the same car park.

There is a path the whole way and easy to follow. The initial ascent is steep then more gentle towards Meikle Conval summit.

Continue over the hill, down the other side and join the path up Little Conval. There is a land rover track that winds up Little Conval if you want a gentler slope. Several cairns on the top of Little Conval.

Return can either be by back over Meikle Conval (possibly shorter) or alongside it, adjacent to the forest. You rejoin the road and walk back to the car park from there.

An alternative route would be starting from the Dufftown golf club, walking to the junction between the two Convals and going up and down them.

Worth doing the two together, or even three with Ben Rinnes. Route back from Little Conval could be the same way - shorter but a hill to climb again - or around Meikle Conval and rejoin the road to the west.
track_title: Convals from Ben Rinnes car park
